snippet: The operative, who was previously known only by the nom de guerre Abu Souleymane, is Abdelilah Himich, a 27-year-old from Morocco, the State Department said....
abstract: State Dept identifies Moroccan man Abdelilah Himich, known previously only by nom de guerre Abu Souleymane al-Faransi, as suspect in terrorist attacks on Paris and Brussels and possible Islamic State operative.

byline.contributor: Eric Schmitt and Aurelien Breeden contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: The operative, who was previously known only by the nom de guerre Abu Souleymane, is Abdelilah Himich, a 27-year-old from Morocco, the State Department said.

headline.main: ISIS Operative Suspected in Paris and Brussels Attacks Is Identified
headline.print_headline: State Dept. Identifies ISIS Operative Suspected in Paris and Brussels Plots
